## Post 1 (2026)

Everyone's giving AI advice. Most of it is garbage.

"Fire your team and replace them with AI." 
"Automate everything." 
"Let AI handle all your work."

Sounds smart. Will set you back years.

I've implemented AI across every department in my companies. Here's what actually works vs what just sounds good on LinkedIn:

Fire your team and replace them with AI → Use AI to empower your team, not replace them. Work is more fun with people.

Automate everything immediately → Fix the process first, then automate. Automating broken processes just makes them broken faster.

Let AI make your business decisions → Use AI for insights, not final judgement. AI still hallucinates.

Replace all brainstorming with AI → AI supports creativity, but humans innovate. AI can only reference what existed before.

Feed AI as much data as possible → Better prompts need better context, not more. Too much data = context rot.

Copy-paste other people's prompts → Build prompts around your own needs. Generic prompts create generic output.

AI automatically gives you an advantage → Your advantage comes from how you use it, not just using it.

